<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALTECH GETS $1 MILLION FOR SCIENCE FELLOWSHIPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PASADENA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Weingart Foundation has donated $1 million to Caltech to establish the Dr. 
Lee A. DuBridge Postdoctoral Prize Fellows Award Fund, which will be used for 
postdoctoral fellowships in physical sciences research. Each award will provide 
a stipend of $30,000 a year for three years. DuBridge served as president of 
Caltech from 1946 to 1969. 
</P>
