<P>
Photo, PICK OF THE WEEK: Claremont Heritage docents will lead a 1 1/4-hour 
walking tour this Saturday of the village area, historic Victorians and college 
and commercial buildings. The tour will start at 10 a.m. at Sumitomo Bank, 102 
Yale Ave. The cost is $2. The group, founded in 1976, began the tours as part 
of Claremont's centennial celebration in 1987 and has continued them on the 
first Saturday of each month. The preservation organization also sponsors 
workshops for owners of older houses, history lectures, slide shows in the 
schools, and it maintains a library on history and restoration. Its main 
