<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALTECH GETS $800,000 FOR GENETIC RESEARCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PASADENA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The L.K. Whittier Foundation of South Pasadena has awarded $800,000 to Caltech 
in support of DNA diagnostics research. Leroy Hood, professor of biology, heads 
the research team, which has developed a new DNA diagnostics procedure that 
distinguishes normal genes from disease-causing genes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
