<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: BUSH TO ATTEND CITIZENSHIP RITES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Bush will participate at an outdoor naturalization ceremony for 3,500 
new U.S. citizens at East Los Angeles College stadium on Sept. 16, Mexican 
Independence Day. 
</P>
<P>
Immigration and Naturalization Service officials said the President agreed to 
appear in East Los Angeles after it was learned that virtually all of the 
prospective citizens are of Mexican descent. 
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, organizers of the annual Mexican Independence Day parade in East Los 
Angeles have moved the event up a day from Sunday, Sept. 17, in an attempt to 
persuade the President to ride in the parade after the ceremony. The White 
House so far has been silent on whether he might appear. 
</P>
<P>
The events are part of the observance of Mexico's revolt for independence from 
Spain, which was ignited by a shout of freedom -- El Grito -- by a priest, 
Miguel Hidalgo y Costilla, in 1810. 
</P>
</TEXT>
