<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
2 OFF-RAMPS TO CLOSE ON COSTA MESA FREEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Motorists who use the southbound Costa Mesa Freeway are in for a jolt this 
month: Heavily used off-ramps at Dyer Road and McFadden Avenue will be closed 
because of freeway-related reconstruction work, Caltrans officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Beginning Monday, the eastbound Dyer Road off-ramp will be closed from the 
southbound Costa Mesa Freeway for about a month. 
</P>
<P>
A week later, on Sunday, Aug. 13, the old McFadden off-ramp from the southbound 
Costa Mesa Freeway will be closed permanently. The new McFadden off-ramp is 
scheduled to open by the end of the month, according to Caltrans spokesman 
Albert Miranda. 
</P>
<P>
"Because many commuters rely on these ramps, we suggest Edinger Avenue and 
MacArthur Boulevard as alternate routes for those commuting in the area," 
Miranda said. 
</P>
<P>
Caltrans officials said they fear negative reaction to the closures because 
there has not been much advance warning. 
</P>
<P>
"We found out about this at the last minute from our field staff," said Kristen 
Argo, an aide to Miranda. 
</P>
</TEXT>
