<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: RETAILING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Mary Ann Galante, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two Orange County investors have paid $2.87 million for the Riverside Auto 
Center in Riverside, according to Sperry Van Ness, a real estate brokerage 
firm. 
