<P>
LIBRARY TEMPORARILY CLOSED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Central Library on Walnut Street will be closed until Sept. 17 for part of 
a $2.4-million renovation. 
</P>
<P>
Branch libraries will remain open for additional hours while the Central 
Library is closed. The Allendale, Hastings, Hill Avenue, Lamanda Park, La 
Pintoresca and Santa Catalina branches will be open from 10 a.m. to 9 p.m. 
Mondays through Thursdays and 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. Fridays and Saturdays. The 
Linda Vista and San Rafael branches will be open from 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. Mondays 
through Saturdays. 
</P>
<P>
In the next month, new carpeting and lighting fixtures will be installed, and 
tables and chairs will be refinished at the Central Library. The remaining 
work, improving the children's room and the building's exterior, will be 
completed next year. 
