<P>
RENEWAL STUDY ORDERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council has ordered a study to determine whether neighborhoods along 
Long Beach Boulevard and Atlantic Avenue should be declared redevelopment 
zones. 
</P>
<P>
The study area, running roughly from Anaheim Street to the Signal Hill border 
and the San Diego Freeway, is somewhat blighted. There are many vacant lots; 
some longtime auto dealerships on Long Beach Boulevard will move to the city's 
new auto mall when it opens, and light rail construction has disrupted some 
businesses. 
</P>
<P>
If parts of the area are eventually included in redevelopment zones, the city 
Redevelopment Agency could condemn property, buy land and sell it to businesses 
to encourage commercial or residential development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
