<P>
Unfair Trading to Be Discussed: The United States and Japan will discuss U.S. 
allegations that Japan is an unfair trader at a regular meeting of the 
bilateral trade committee, scheduled for September. "We can use this meeting to 
clarify what the United States is saying without actually negotiating with 
them," which will save face for the Japanese, a trade official for that country 
said. Tokyo protested vehemently when Washington charged Japan at the end of 
May with unfair trading practices in supercomputers, wood products and 
